Bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy due to Chlamydia pneumoniae infection. We here report a 5-year-old boy who presented with cough and bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy with a family history of sarcoidosis. The laboratory investigations did not confirm this diagnosis. The child was serologically proven to have Chlamydia pneumoniae infection. He responded well to a course of erythromycin resulting in complete resolution of his symptoms and the presenting radiographic findings on his initial chest X-ray. Pediatr. Pulmonol. 2011 46:1038-1040. Â© 2011 Wiley-Liss, Inc.